---
/**
 * /en/about/ — About NilaTales (English).
 */
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About · NilaTales"
  description="About NilaTales — illustrated bedtime stories for children."
  locale="en"
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 prose-ta">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-bold text-kohl-900 mb-2">About NilaTales</h1>
    <p class="text-kohl-500 font-rounded italic mb-8" lang="ta">நிலா கதைகள் பற்றி</p>

    <p class="text-base text-kohl-700 leading-relaxed">
      <em>Nila</em> means moon. <em>Katai</em> means story. NilaTales is stories told under
      moonlight — bedtime stories from amma, appa, paatti, and thatha.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-base text-kohl-700 leading-relaxed">
      NilaTales is a quiet place for children (ages 3–12) and the grown-ups who read
      with them. We tell three kinds of stories:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-kohl-700">
      <li><strong>Thirukkural Stories</strong> — Valluvar's 1330 couplets, one short story at a time.</li>
      <li><strong>Panchatantra Tales</strong> — Ancient Indian fables of clever animals and wise lessons.</li>
      <li><strong>Moral Stories</strong> — Original tales about kindness, courage, and friendship.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-6 text-base text-kohl-700 leading-relaxed">
      We also have comics, lullabies, and printable activities — all designed for
      cozy bedtime reading.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-base text-kohl-700 leading-relaxed">
      NilaTales is a sister site of
      <a href="https://nitvi.kingspath.in" class="text-twilight-500 hover:text-twilight-700 underline">NitviTalks</a>,
      part of the Kingspath family — bringing STEM education and storytelling to children.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-paper-200">
      <p class="text-sm text-kohl-500">
        Made with care under the moon. 🌙
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>